node.title: Two arrested after aggravated robberies in Tauranga
node.description: Two men, aged 18 and 21, have been arrested in relation to two aggravated robberies in Tauranga.
node.content:
["Two men, aged 18 and 21, have been arrested in relation to two aggravated robberies in Tauranga.", "", "
\nPhoto: RNZ / Claire Eastham-Farrelly\n
", "Police said the robberies occurred on Bethlehem Road and Minden Road on 4 January in the evening.", "The 18-year-old is charged with one count of aggravated robbery.", "The 21-year-old is facing two charges of aggravated robbery, as well as cruelty/ill-treatment of an animal.", "They are to appear in Tauranga District Court on 8 January."]
